# ClaudeTube Agent Integration

When the user shares a YouTube URL, asks to play/watch a video, or wants queue control while coding, use ClaudeTube.

## Preferred: agent inbox

Write JSON to `.claudetube/inbox.json` in the workspace root:

```json
{ "action": "play", "url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VIDEO_ID" }
```

Read playback state from `.claudetube/status.json` (updated automatically).

## Actions

| Action | Payload |
|--------|---------|
| Play | `{ "action": "play", "url": "..." }` or `{ "action": "play", "videoId": "..." }` |
| Enqueue | `{ "action": "enqueue", "url": "..." }` |
| Next / skip | `{ "action": "next" }` |
| Toggle | `{ "action": "toggle" }` |
| Mute | `{ "action": "mute" }` |
| Seek | `{ "action": "seek", "seconds": 120 }` |
| Show sidebar | `{ "action": "show" }` |
| Clear queue | `{ "action": "clearQueue" }` |
| Layout | `{ "action": "setLayout", "layout": "mini" }` |
| Speed | `{ "action": "setPlaybackRate", "rate": 1.5 }` |

Layouts: `compact`, `theater`, `mini`

## Shell helper

```bash
./scripts/claudetube-agent.sh play "URL"
./scripts/claudetube-agent.sh next
./scripts/claudetube-agent.sh seek 120
./scripts/claudetube-agent.sh layout mini
```

## Tips

- For tutorials, use `mini` layout and 1.25–1.5x speed.
- Check `status.json` before seeking or skipping.
- Playlist URLs are supported.
